{{citation needed|November 5 (Lunisolar)}}

{{Lunisolar November}} '''November 5''' is the 5th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Enryaku|ja|延暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 16th year（[[Julian calendar]] [[797]] [[November 27]]） – {{ill|Sakanoue no Tamuramaro|ja|坂上田村麻呂|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} was appointed as {{ill|Shogun|ja|将軍|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} for the subjugation of the Ezo lands. * {{ill|Bunryaku|ja|文暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1234]] [[November 27]]） – Due to a celestial earthquake, the era name was changed from {{ill|Tennpuku (Japan)|ja|天福|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} to {{ill|Bunryaku|ja|文暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} via {{ill|Era change|ja|改元|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[1854]] [[December 24]]） – During the 【Ansei great earthquake】 (安政の大Earthquake / {{ill|Ansei Nankai Earthquake|ja|安政南海Earthquake|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}), a massive tsunami caused 80,000 households to be swept away with over 3,000 fatalities. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1857]] [[December 20]]） – {{ill|Yoshida Shōin|ja|吉田松陰|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} opened the {{ill|Matsushita Sonjuku|ja|松下村塾|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Births == * {{ill|Eikyō|ja|永享|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1432]] [[November 27]]） – {{ill|Shimazu Tadatoki|ja|島津立久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a regional warlord (守護大名) of the Shimazu clan (died [[1474]]). * {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 8th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1723]] [[December 2]]） – {{ill|Satake Yoshiaki|ja|佐竹義明|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a daimyō (died [[1758]]). * {{ill|Kansei|ja|寛政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1791]] [[November 30]]） – {{ill|Ii Naotaka|ja|井伊直暉|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a daimyō (died [[1826]]). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1820]] [[December 10]]） – {{ill|Matsudaira Terutoku|ja|松平輝徳|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a daimyō (died [[1840]]). * Bunsei 10th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1827]] [[December 22]]） – {{ill|Zeisho Atsu|ja|税所篤|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a samurai and bureaucrat (died [[1910]]). * Bunsei 13rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1830]] [[December 19]]） – {{ill|Sakakibara Kanekichi|ja|榊原鍵吉|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a retainer (幕臣) and practitioner of {{ill|Kenjutsu|ja|剣術|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (died [[1894]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Tennen|ja|天永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1111]] [[December 7]]） – {{ill|Ōe Masafusa|ja|大江匡房|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a kugyō, Confucian scholar, and poet (born [[1041]]). * {{ill|Genkyū|ja|元久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1204]] [[November 27]]） – {{ill|Hojo Masanori|ja|北条政範|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander (武将) (born [[1189]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 10th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1839]] [[December 10]]） – {{ill|Matsudaira Saiatsu|ja|松平斉厚|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a daimyō (born [[1783]]). * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1856]] [[December 2]]） – {{ill|Ashidai Hirokun|ja|足代弘訓|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a kokugakuist (born [[1785]]). * {{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1869]] [[December 7]]） – {{ill|Ōmura Masujirō|ja|大村益次郎|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military scholar (born [[1824]]).
