{{Lunisolar November|qq=}} '''November 5''' is the 5th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=}} the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Enryaku|ja|延暦|qq=}} 16th year（[[Julian calendar]] [[797]] [[November 27]]） – {{ill|Sakanoue no Tamuramaro|ja|坂上田村麻呂|qq=}} was appointed as {{ill|Shogun|ja|将軍|qq=}} for the subjugation of the Ezo lands. * {{ill|Bunryaku|ja|文暦|qq=}} 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1234]] [[November 27]]） – Due to a celestial earthquake, the era name was changed from {{ill|Tennpuku (Japan)|ja|天福|qq=}} to {{ill|Bunryaku|ja|文暦|qq=}} via {{ill|Era change|ja|改元|qq=}}. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|qq=}} 1st year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[1854]] [[December 24]]） – During the 【Ansei great earthquake】 (安政の大Earthquake / {{ill|Ansei Nankai Earthquake|ja|安政南海Earthquake|qq=}}), a massive tsunami caused 80,000 households to be swept away with over 3,000 fatalities. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|qq=}} 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1857]] [[December 20]]） – {{ill|Yoshida Shōin|ja|吉田松陰|qq=}} opened the {{ill|Matsushita Sonjuku|ja|松下村塾|qq=}}.
