{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十一月初五|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 11월 5일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar November|qq=}} '''November 5''' is the 5th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=|12=draft}} the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Enryaku|ja|延暦|qq=|12=draft}} 16th year（[[Julian calendar]] [[797]] [[November 27]]） – {{ill|Sakanoue no Tamuramaro|ja|坂上田村麻呂|qq=|12=draft}} was appointed as {{ill|Shogun|ja|将軍|qq=|12=draft}} for the subjugation of the Ezo lands. * {{ill|Bunryaku|ja|文暦|qq=|12=draft}} 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1234]] [[November 27]]） – Due to a celestial earthquake, the era name was changed from {{ill|Tennpuku (Japan)|ja|天福|qq=|12=draft}} to {{ill|Bunryaku|ja|文暦|qq=|12=draft}} via {{ill|Era change|ja|改元|qq=|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|qq=|12=draft}} 1st year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[1854]] [[December 24]]） – During the 【Ansei great earthquake】 (安政の大Earthquake / {{ill|Ansei Nankai Earthquake|ja|安政南海Earthquake|qq=|12=draft}}), a massive tsunami caused 80,000 households to be swept away with over 3,000 fatalities. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|qq=|12=draft}} 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1857]] [[December 20]]） – {{ill|Yoshida Shōin|ja|吉田松陰|qq=|12=draft}} opened the {{ill|Matsushita Sonjuku|ja|松下村塾|qq=|12=draft}}.
== Births == * {{ill|Eikyō|ja|永享|qq=|12=draft}} 4th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1432]] [[November 27]]） – {{ill|Shimazu Tadatoki|ja|島津立久|qq=|12=draft}}, a regional warlord (守護大名) of the Shimazu clan (died [[1474]]). * {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|qq=|12=draft}} 8th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1723]] [[December 2]]） – {{ill|Satake Yoshiaki|ja|佐竹義明|qq=|12=draft}}, a daimyō (died [[1758]]). * {{ill|Kansei|ja|寛政|qq=|12=draft}} 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1791]] [[November 30]]） – {{ill|Ii Naotaka|ja|井伊直暉|qq=|12=draft}}, a daimyō (died [[1826]]). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|qq=|12=draft}} 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1820]] [[December 10]]） – {{ill|Matsudaira Terutoku|ja|松平輝徳|qq=|12=draft}}, a daimyō (died [[1840]]). * Bunsei 10th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1827]] [[December 22]]） – {{ill|Zeisho Atsu|ja|税所篤|qq=|12=draft}}, a samurai and bureaucrat (died [[1910]]). * Bunsei 13rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1830]] [[December 19]]） – {{ill|Sakakibara Kanekichi|ja|榊原鍵吉|qq=|12=draft}}, a retainer (幕臣) and practitioner of {{ill|Kenjutsu|ja|剣術|qq=|12=draft}} (died [[1894]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Tennen|ja|天永|qq=|12=draft}} 2nd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1111]] [[December 7]]） – {{ill|Ōe Masafusa|ja|大江匡房|qq=|12=draft}}, a kugyō, Confucian scholar, and poet (born [[1041]]). * {{ill|Genkyū|ja|元久|qq=|12=draft}} 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1204]] [[November 27]]） – {{ill|Hojo Masanori|ja|北条政範|qq=|12=draft}}, a military commander (武将) (born [[1189]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|qq=|12=draft}} 10th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1839]] [[December 10]]） – {{ill|Matsudaira Saiatsu|ja|松平斉厚|qq=|12=draft}}, a daimyō (born [[1783]]). * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|qq=|12=draft}} 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1856]] [[December 2]]） – {{ill|Ashidai Hirokun|ja|足代弘訓|qq=|12=draft}}, a kokugakuist (born [[1785]]). * {{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|12=draft}} 2nd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1869]] [[December 7]]） – {{ill|Ōmura Masujirō|ja|大村益次郎|qq=|12=draft}}, a military scholar (born [[1824]]).
