== Births == * [[:en:Eikyō|Eikyō]] 4th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1432|1432]] [[November 27]]） – {{ill|Shimazu Tadatoki|ja|島津立久|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimazu Tadatoki|qq=}}, a regional warlord (守護大名) of the Shimazu clan (died [[:en:1474|1474]]). * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 8th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1723|1723]] [[December 2]]） – [[:en:Satake Yoshiharu|Satake Yoshiaki]], a daimyō (died [[1758]]). * [[:en:Kansei|Kansei]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1791]] [[November 30]]） – {{ill|Ii Naotaka|ja|井伊直暉|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ii Naotaka|qq=}}, a daimyō (died [[1826]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1820]] [[December 10]]） – {{ill|Matsudaira Terutoku|ja|松平輝徳|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsudaira Terutoku|qq=}}, a daimyō (died [[1840]]). * Bunsei 10th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1827]] [[December 22]]） – [[:en:Saisho Atsushi|Zeisho Atsu]], a samurai and bureaucrat (died [[1910]]). * Bunsei 13rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1830]] [[December 19]]） – [[:en:Sakakibara Kenkichi|Sakakibara Kanekichi]], a retainer (幕臣) and practitioner of [[:en:Kenjutsu|Kenjutsu]] (died [[1894]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Ten'ei|Tennen]] 2nd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1111|1111]] [[December 7]]） – [[:en:Ōe no Masafusa|Ōe Masafusa]], a kugyō, Confucian scholar, and poet (born [[:en:1041|1041]]). * [[:en:Genkyū|Genkyū]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1204|1204]] [[November 27]]） – {{ill|Hojo Masanori|ja|北条政範|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hojo Masanori|qq=}}, a military commander (武将) (born [[:en:1189|1189]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 10th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1839]] [[December 10]]） – {{ill|Matsudaira Saiatsu|ja|松平斉厚|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsudaira Saiatsu|qq=}}, a daimyō (born [[1783]]). * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1856]] [[December 2]]） – {{ill|Ashidai Hirokun|ja|足代弘訓|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashidai Hirokun|qq=}}, a kokugakuist (born [[1785]]). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 2nd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1869]] [[December 7]]） – [[:en:Ōmura Masujirō|Ōmura Masujirō]], a military scholar (born [[1824]]).
