== Events == * [[:en:Enryaku|Enryaku]] 16th year（[[Julian calendar]] [[:en:797|797]] [[November 27]]） – [[:en:Sakanoue no Tamuramaro|Sakanoue no Tamuramaro]] was appointed as {{ill|Shogun|ja|将軍|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shogun|qq=}} for the subjugation of the Ezo lands. * [[:en:Bunryaku|Bunryaku]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1234|1234]] [[November 27]]） – Due to a celestial earthquake, the era name was changed from {{ill|Tennpuku (Japan)|ja|天福|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tennpuku (Japan)|qq=}} to [[:en:Bunryaku|Bunryaku]] via {{ill|Era change|ja|改元|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Era change|qq=}}. * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 1st year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1854|1854]] [[December 24]]） – During the 【Ansei great earthquake】 (安政の大Earthquake / {{ill|Ansei Nankai Earthquake|ja|安政南海Earthquake|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ansei Nankai Earthquake|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}), a massive tsunami caused 80,000 households to be swept away with over 3,000 fatalities. * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1857|1857]] [[December 20]]） – [[:en:Yoshida Shōin|Yoshida Shōin]] opened the [[:en:Shōkasonjuku Academy|Matsushita Sonjuku]].
== Births == * [[:en:Eikyō|Eikyō]] 4th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1432|1432]] [[November 27]]） – {{ill|Shimazu Tadatoki|ja|島津立久|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimazu Tadatoki|qq=}}, a regional warlord (守護大名) of the Shimazu clan (died [[:en:1474|1474]]). * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 8th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1723|1723]] [[December 2]]） – [[:en:Satake Yoshiharu|Satake Yoshiaki]], a daimyō (died [[:en:1758|1758]]). * [[:en:Kansei|Kansei]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1791|1791]] [[November 30]]） – {{ill|Ii Naotaka|ja|井伊直暉|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ii Naotaka|qq=}}, a daimyō (died [[:en:1826|1826]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1820|1820]] [[December 10]]） – {{ill|Matsudaira Terutoku|ja|松平輝徳|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsudaira Terutoku|qq=}}, a daimyō (died [[:en:1840|1840]]). * Bunsei 10th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1827|1827]] [[December 22]]） – [[:en:Saisho Atsushi|Zeisho Atsu]], a samurai and bureaucrat (died [[:en:1910|1910]]). * Bunsei 13rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1830|1830]] [[December 19]]） – [[:en:Sakakibara Kenkichi|Sakakibara Kanekichi]], a retainer (幕臣) and practitioner of [[:en:Kenjutsu|Kenjutsu]] (died [[:en:1894|1894]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Ten'ei|Tennen]] 2nd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1111|1111]] [[December 7]]） – [[:en:Ōe no Masafusa|Ōe Masafusa]], a kugyō, Confucian scholar, and poet (born [[:en:1041|1041]]). * [[:en:Genkyū|Genkyū]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1204|1204]] [[November 27]]） – {{ill|Hojo Masanori|ja|北条政範|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hojo Masanori|qq=}}, a military commander (武将) (born [[:en:1189|1189]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 10th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1839|1839]] [[December 10]]） – {{ill|Matsudaira Saiatsu|ja|松平斉厚|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsudaira Saiatsu|qq=}}, a daimyō (born [[:en:1783|1783]]). * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1856|1856]] [[December 2]]） – {{ill|Ashidai Hirokun|ja|足代弘訓|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashidai Hirokun|qq=}}, a kokugakuist (born [[:en:1785|1785]]). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 2nd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1869|1869]] [[December 7]]） – [[:en:Ōmura Masujirō|Ōmura Masujirō]], a military scholar (born [[:en:1824|1824]]).
