{{Not to be confused with|November 5|qq=November 5}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十一月初五|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 11월 5일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar November|qq=}} '''November 5''' is the 5th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}} the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senbu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Enryaku|Enryaku]] 16th year（[[Julian calendar]] [[:en:797|797]] [[November 27]]） – [[:en:Sakanoue no Tamuramaro|Sakanoue no Tamuramaro]] was appointed as {{ill|Shogun|ja|将軍|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shogun|qq=}} for the subjugation of the Ezo lands. * [[:en:Bunryaku|Bunryaku]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1234|1234]] [[November 27]]） – Due to a celestial earthquake, the era name was changed from {{ill|Tennpuku (Japan)|ja|天福|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tennpuku (Japan)|qq=}} to [[:en:Bunryaku|Bunryaku]] via {{ill|Era change|ja|改元|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Era change|qq=}}. * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 1st year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1854|1854]] [[December 24]]） – During the 【Ansei great earthquake】 (安政の大Earthquake / {{ill|Ansei Nankai Earthquake|ja|安政南海Earthquake|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ansei Nankai Earthquake|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}), a massive tsunami caused 80,000 households to be swept away with over 3,000 fatalities. * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1857|1857]] [[December 20]]） – [[:en:Yoshida Shōin|Yoshida Shōin]] opened the [[:en:Shōkasonjuku Academy|Matsushita Sonjuku]].
== Births == * [[:en:Eikyō|Eikyō]] 4th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1432|1432]] [[November 27]]） – {{ill|Shimazu Tadatoki|ja|島津立久|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimazu Tadatoki|qq=}}, a regional warlord (守護大名) of the Shimazu clan (died [[:en:1474|1474]]). * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 8th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1723|1723]] [[:en:December 2|December 2]]） – [[:en:Satake Yoshiharu|Satake Yoshiaki]], a daimyō (died [[:en:1758|1758]]). * [[:en:Kansei|Kansei]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1791|1791]] [[November 30]]） – {{ill|Ii Naotaka|ja|井伊直暉|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ii Naotaka|qq=}}, a daimyō (died [[:en:1826|1826]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1820|1820]] [[:en:December 10|December 10]]） – {{ill|Matsudaira Terutoku|ja|松平輝徳|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsudaira Terutoku|qq=}}, a daimyō (died [[:en:1840|1840]]). * Bunsei 10th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1827|1827]] [[December 22]]） – [[:en:Saisho Atsushi|Zeisho Atsu]], a samurai and bureaucrat (died [[:en:1910|1910]]). * Bunsei 13rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1830|1830]] [[:en:December 19|December 19]]） – [[:en:Sakakibara Kenkichi|Sakakibara Kanekichi]], a retainer (幕臣) and practitioner of [[:en:Kenjutsu|Kenjutsu]] (died [[:en:1894|1894]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Ten'ei|Tennen]] 2nd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1111|1111]] [[December 7]]） – [[:en:Ōe no Masafusa|Ōe Masafusa]], a kugyō, Confucian scholar, and poet (born [[:en:1041|1041]]). * [[:en:Genkyū|Genkyū]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1204|1204]] [[November 27]]） – {{ill|Hojo Masanori|ja|北条政範|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hojo Masanori|qq=}}, a military commander (武将) (born [[:en:1189|1189]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 10th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1839|1839]] [[:en:December 10|December 10]]） – {{ill|Matsudaira Saiatsu|ja|松平斉厚|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsudaira Saiatsu|qq=}}, a daimyō (born [[:en:1783|1783]]). * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1856|1856]] [[:en:December 2|December 2]]） – {{ill|Ashidai Hirokun|ja|足代弘訓|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashidai Hirokun|qq=}}, a kokugakuist (born [[:en:1785|1785]]). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 2nd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1869|1869]] [[December 7]]） – [[:en:Ōmura Masujirō|Ōmura Masujirō]], a military scholar (born [[:en:1824|1824]]).
