== Births == * [[:en:Eikyō|Eikyō]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1432|1432]] [[:en:November 27|November 27]]） – {{ill|Shimazu Tadatoki|ja|島津立久|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimazu Tadatoki|qq=|1=Shimazu Tatsuhisa|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11245262}}, a regional warlord (守護大名) of the Shimazu clan (died [[:en:1474|1474]]). * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 8th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1723|1723]] [[:en:December 2|December 2]]） – [[:en:Satake Yoshiharu|Satake Yoshiaki]], a daimyō (died [[:en:1758|1758]]). * [[:en:Kansei|Kansei]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1791|1791]] [[:en:November 30|November 30]]） – {{ill|Ii Naotaka|ja|井伊直暉|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ii Naotaka|qq=|1=Ii Naoteru|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11161312}}, a daimyō (died [[:en:1826|1826]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1820|1820]] [[:en:December 10|December 10]]） – {{ill|Matsudaira Terutoku|ja|松平輝徳|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsudaira Terutoku|qq=|1=Matsudaira Teruakira|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11530597}}, a daimyō (died [[:en:1840|1840]]). * Bunsei 10th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1827|1827]] [[:en:December 22|December 22]]） – [[:en:Saisho Atsushi|Zeisho Atsu]], a samurai and bureaucrat (died [[:en:1910|1910]]). * Bunsei 13rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1830|1830]] [[:en:December 19|December 19]]） – [[:en:Sakakibara Kenkichi|Sakakibara Kanekichi]], a retainer (幕臣) and practitioner of [[:en:Kenjutsu|Kenjutsu]] (died [[:en:1894|1894]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Ten'ei|Tennen]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1111|1111]] [[:en:December 7|December 7]]） – [[:en:Ōe no Masafusa|Ōe Masafusa]], a kugyō, Confucian scholar, and poet (born [[:en:1041|1041]]). * [[:en:Genkyū|Genkyū]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1204|1204]] [[:en:November 27|November 27]]） – {{ill|Hojo Masanori|ja|北条政範|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hojo Masanori|qq=|1=Hōjō Masanori|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11402108}}, a military commander (武将) (born [[:en:1189|1189]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 10th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1839|1839]] [[:en:December 10|December 10]]） – {{ill|Matsudaira Saiatsu|ja|松平斉厚|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsudaira Saiatsu|qq=|1=Matsudaira Nariatsu|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11530458}}, a daimyō (born [[:en:1783|1783]]). * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1856|1856]] [[:en:December 2|December 2]]） – {{ill|Ashidai Hirokun|ja|足代弘訓|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashidai Hirokun|qq=|1=Hironori Ajiro|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q6535014}}, a kokugakuist (born [[:en:1785|1785]]). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1869|1869]] [[:en:December 7|December 7]]） – [[:en:Ōmura Masujirō|Ōmura Masujirō]], a military scholar (born [[:en:1824|1824]]).
